{"type":"message","id":"f39f0aa9","parentId":"53547095","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:48:38.177Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 20:48 GMT+2] OPERATION: OODA FIX & SYNERGY RESEARCH.\n\n1.  **OODA Loop (Linting Fix):**\n    *   *Target Files:* `scripts/log_compressor.py`, `scripts/run_archivist.py`, `src/core/network.py`.\n    *   *Action:* Apply PEP 8 formatting (blank lines, imports).\n    *   *Verify:* Run `scripts/safe_commit.py \"fix: Resolve PEP8 linting errors in system scripts\"`.\n    *   *Constraint:* Must see \"COMMIT SUCCESS\".\n\n2.  **Synergy Research (Hierarchical Agents):**\n    *   *Search:* \"LLM Context Handover JSON-Spec\", \"Log Analysis Pattern Recognition LLM\", \"Autonomous Agent Error Correction Loop\".\n    *   *Goal:* Find a standard format for Pro -> Flash delegation (e.g., \"Task JSON\" vs \"Natural Language\").\n\n3.  **Synthesis (v6.0 Proposal):**\n    *   *Context Handover:* Proposal for `TASK_SPEC.json` (Structured delegation).\n    *   *Active Archiving:* \"Log Anomaly Vectorization\" (Redis Stack).\n    *   *Flash Autonomy:* \"Auto-Fix Manifest\" (If error is `flake8`, Flash fixes without asking).\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Commit Status (Real log).\n    *   Research Findings.\n    *   v6.0 Upgrade Plan."}],"timestamp":1771354118175}}
{"type":"message","id":"349ea468","parentId":"f39f0aa9","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:49:13.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Project Requirements**\n\nI've just finished dissecting the user's initial prompt. The core requirement is clear: I must implement a code fix by addressing specific PEP 8 issues in the designated Python files. Right now, I'm focusing on the first step: identifying and resolving any linting issues.\n\n\n**Planning the Code Changes**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the code changes. The plan is to get the linter running across the three files and implement the fixes according to PEP 8 standards. After that, I will push the changes, as instructed.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771354153408_55","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/log_compressor.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771354153515_56","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/run_archivist.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771354153633_57","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/network.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4746,"output":148,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4894,"cost":{"input":0.009492,"output":0.001776,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011268}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771354118177}}
{"type":"message","id":"04ecdcb5","parentId":"349ea468","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:49:13.661Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771354153408_55","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport glob\n\ndef compress_logs():\n    log_files = glob.glob('logs/*.log')\n    all_lines = []\n\n    for log_file in log_files:\n        try:\n            with open(log_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                all_lines.extend(f.readlines())\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error reading {log_file}: {e}\")\n            continue\n\n    # Deduplicate lines while preserving order\n    seen = set()\n    unique_lines = []\n    for line in all_lines:\n        if line not in seen:\n            unique_lines.append(line)\n            seen.add(line)\n\n    # Join lines\n    content = \"\".join(unique_lines)\n\n    # Limit to last 50,000 characters\n    limit = 50000\n    if len(content) > limit:\n        content = content[-limit:]\n        # Try to cut at a newline to be cleaner\n        first_newline = content.find('\\n')\n        if first_newline != -1:\n             content = content[first_newline+1:]\n\n    output_path = 'logs/compressed_context.md'\n    try:\n        with open(output_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            f.write(\"# Compressed Log Context\\n\\n\")\n            f.write(content)\n        print(f\"Successfully compressed logs to {output_path}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error writing to {output_path}: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    compress_logs()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771354153659}}
{"type":"message","id":"e53c69fb","parentId":"04ecdcb5","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:49:13.666Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771354153515_56","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport glob\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport random\n\n\ndef run_archivist():\n    log_files = glob.glob(\"logs/*.log\")\n    combined_logs = \"\"\n\n    print(f\"Found {len(log_files)} log files.\")\n\n    # Simulate reading tail of logs\n    for log_file in log_files:\n        try:\n            with open(log_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                # Read last 2000 chars approx (simplified tail)\n                f.seek(0, 2)\n                size = f.tell()\n                f.seek(max(size - 4000, 0), 0)\n                combined_logs += f\"\\n--- {log_file} ---\\n\" + f.read()\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error reading {log_file}: {e}\")\n\n    # Output directory\n    os.makedirs(\"reports\", exist_ok=True)\n    output_file = \"reports/ARCHIVIST_VERDICT.md\"\n\n    print(\"Analyzing logs...\")\n    # Mocking the analysis for speed/reliability in this test context\n    # In a real scenario, this would call an LLM API\n\n    verdict = f\"\"\"# Archivist Verdict\n**Date:** {time.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")}\n**Status:** HEALTHY\n\n## Analysis\nScanned {len(log_files)} log sources.\n\n- **Errors:** None critical detected.\n- **Warnings:** Nominal.\n- **System Integrity:** Verified.\n\n## Action Items\n- Continue monitoring `logs/` folder.\n- Run cleanup on old logs > 30 days.\n\"\"\"\n\n    with open(output_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(verdict)\n\n    print(f\"Verdict written to {output_file}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    run_archivist()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771354153665}}
{"type":"message","id":"313f4200","parentId":"e53c69fb","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:49:13.670Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771354153633_57","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import httpx\nimport asyncio\nimport orjson\nimport logging\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    level=logging.INFO,\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\n    filename='logs/network.log'\n)\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nclass HFTClient:\n    \"\"\"\n    High-Frequency Trading Client wrapper around httpx.AsyncClient.\n    Optimized for HTTP/2, connection reuse, and strict parsing.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, worker_id: int = 0, base_url: str = \"https://api.dmarket.com\"):\n        self.worker_id = worker_id\n        self.base_url = base_url\n        self.client: Optional[httpx.AsyncClient] = None\n        self._etag_cache: Dict[str, str] = {}\n\n        # Security: Treat all inputs as untrusted (concept)\n        # We use orjson for strict and fast JSON parsing\n\n    async def __aenter__(self):\n        # Startup Offset: Prevent thundering herd\n        delay = self.worker_id * 0.15\n        if delay > 0:\n            logger.info(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} delaying startup by {delay:.2f}s\")\n            await asyncio.sleep(delay)\n\n        limits = httpx.Limits(max_keepalive_connections=20, max_connections=20)\n        self.client = httpx.AsyncClient(\n            base_url=self.base_url,\n            http2=True,\n            limits=limits,\n            timeout=10.0,\n            headers={\n                \"User-Agent\": f\"OpenClaw-HFT/1.0 (Worker {self.worker_id})\",\n                \"Accept\": \"application/json\",\n            }\n        )\n        logger.info(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} initialized HFTClient (HTTP/2 enabled)\")\n        return self\n\n    async def __aexit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):\n        if self.client:\n            await self.client.aclose()\n\n    async def get(self, endpoint: str, params: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Optimized GET request with ETag support and orjson parsing.\n        \"\"\"\n        if not self.client:\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Client not initialized. Use 'async with' context.\")\n\n        headers = {}\n        # Optimization: ETag support\n        if endpoint in self._etag_cache:\n            headers[\"If-None-Match\"] = self._etag_cache[endpoint]\n\n        try:\n            response = await self.client.get(endpoint, params=params, headers=headers)\n\n            # Security / Archivist: Rate Limit Monitoring\n            # Log specific headers if present\n            rl_remain = response.headers.get(\"X-RateLimit-Remaining\")\n            if rl_remain:\n                logger.info(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} | RL-Remain: {rl_remain}\")\n\n            if response.status_code == 304:\n                logger.debug(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} | Hit 304 Not Modified for {endpoint}\")\n                return {\"status\": \"not_modified\"} # signal for caller to use cache if they had one\n\n            if response.status_code == 429:\n                logger.warning(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} | HIT 429 TOO MANY REQUESTS\")\n                return {\"error\": \"rate_limit\", \"status\": 429}\n\n            response.raise_for_status()\n\n            # Capture ETag for next time\n            etag = response.headers.get(\"ETag\")\n            if etag:\n                self._etag_cache[endpoint] = etag\n\n            # Security: Strict JSON parsing with orjson\n            try:\n                return orjson.loads(response.content)\n            except orjson.JSONDecodeError as e:\n                logger.error(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} | JSON Decode Error: {e}\")\n                return {\"error\": \"json_decode_error\"}\n\n        except httpx.HTTPError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Worker {self.worker_id} | HTTP Error: {e}\")\n            return {\"error\": str(e)}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771354153669}}
