{"type":"message","id":"82075741","parentId":"dd09ca06","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:52:20.795Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Diagnosing the PowerShell Issue**\n\nI've homed in on the PowerShell version as the culprit. The `&&` operator, which is causing the error, is only reliable in PowerShell Core 7.0 and later. Given the runtime and node version, it’s a bit of a head-scratcher why this incompatibility is showing up. Further investigation is needed to clarify if we're dealing with a compatibility issue, or maybe the wrong PowerShell version is being invoked.\n\n\n**Investigating Execution Path**\n\nI'm now focusing on the execution environment. Even with `pwsh` indicated, it seems like the `&&` operator is causing problems, suggesting a compatibility issue. To bypass this, I'm now trying separate `git add` and `git commit` commands to see if that resolves the problem. I'm also going to examine the `safe_commit.py` script. The use of `subprocess.run` to call `git` seems correct, which should bypass shell issues, but I'll check for output buffering problems or other invocation errors.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771354340788_68","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python scripts/safe_commit.py \"fix: Resolve PEP8 linting errors in system scripts\" > commit.log 2>&1"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":13775,"output":304,"cacheRead":11545,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14079,"cost":{"input":0.027549999999999998,"output":0.003648,"cacheRead":0.0023090000000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033506999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771354320998}}
